{{nihongo|[[Nomihodai]]|飲み放題|nomihōdai}} is a [[Japanese]] word meaning "drink as much as you like". It refers to a format used in bars and [[izakaya]] in Japan where the customers pay a set price and can then drink as much as they want, usually during a fixed period of time. The nomihodai format often goes hand in hand with [[tabehodai]], "eat as much as you like".